<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="011" project="github-actions-rationalization-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix deploy-infrastructure.yml ghost triggers (P3)</title>
    <phase>1: Fix Broken Workflows</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>ci-cd, github-actions, devops, workflow-fix</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Workflow YAML edit + investigation; FR-04 acceptance criterion; no .cs/.ts modified</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Investigate and fix `deploy-infrastructure.yml` so it does NOT trigger runs on non-matching branches. Per design §2.1 P3: workflow declares triggers limited to `pull_request` + `push to master` + `workflow_dispatch` with path filters, but ghost runs appear on every non-master push with `event: "push"` and `jobs:[]` — same loader-failure pattern as P1. Hypothesis: a YAML loader bug (similar to PR #314's duplicate-key); needs strict review.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform DevOps engineer. Comfortable with strict YAML review, GitHub Actions trigger semantics, and loader-failure patterns (P1 fix in PR #314).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `deploy-infrastructure.yml` is fixed so that pushing a commit to a feature branch with no `infrastructure/bicep/**` changes produces zero `deploy-infrastructure.yml` runs. Fix is &lt;50% replacement OR delete-with-rationale.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design §2.1 P3: ghost-trigger pattern — workflow appears in run history on non-matching pushes with empty `jobs:[]`. Severity HIGH; mechanism unclear; needs investigation. Likely a loader-failure (silently malformed YAML that fails to parse triggers) similar to PR #314's duplicate-key bug.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>.github/workflows/deploy-infrastructure.yml</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/baseline/workflow-inventory-2026-06-01.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-04: Feature-branch push with no `infrastructure/bicep/**` changes produces zero runs</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-02: &lt;50% line replacement OR delete-with-rationale</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-04: Deletion via `git rm`, not comment-out</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-07: `<repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>`</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MUST run `actionlint` locally BEFORE pushing</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/github-actions-rationalization-r1/baseline/workflow-inventory-2026-06-01.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/ci-cd-workflow.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `deploy-infrastructure.yml` end-to-end. Pay strict attention to YAML structure (indentation, duplicate keys, list vs map ambiguity). Check the `on:` clause for `pull_request`, `push`, `workflow_dispatch`.</step>
    <step order="2">Run `actionlint .github/workflows/deploy-infrastructure.yml`. Note any warnings even if not errors. Run a strict YAML linter: `yamllint -d "{rules: {key-duplicates: enable}}" .github/workflows/deploy-infrastructure.yml`.</step>
    <step order="3">Inspect run history: `gh run list --workflow=deploy-infrastructure.yml --limit 30 --json conclusion,event,headBranch,jobs`. Identify ghost-trigger runs (event=push, headBranch≠master, jobs=[]).</step>
    <step order="4">Identify root cause:
      - **Loader-failure pattern**: malformed YAML → GitHub still creates a run but jobs don't load. Look for duplicate keys, bad indentation, missing `paths:` under correct trigger.
      - **Trigger misconfiguration**: missing branch filter on `push:`, or path filter on `push:` rather than `pull_request:`.
    </step>
    <step order="5">Apply minimal fix using Edit tool (&lt;50% replacement). Verify with `actionlint`. Document the root cause in commit message.</step>
    <step order="6">Push to a test branch with no `infrastructure/bicep/**` changes. Confirm `gh run list --workflow=deploy-infrastructure.yml` shows zero new runs for the test push.</step>
    <step order="7">Merge fix commit. Commit message: `fix(ci): eliminate deploy-infrastructure ghost triggers (FR-04)`.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 011 status to ✅ completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="actionlint">Validate workflow YAML</tool>
    <tool name="yamllint">Strict YAML duplicate-key check</tool>
    <tool name="gh">Inspect run history</tool>
    <tool name="Read">Read workflow file</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Apply minimal fix</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="config">.github/workflows/deploy-infrastructure.yml (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">After fix, pushing to a feature branch with no `infrastructure/bicep/**` changes produces 0 `deploy-infrastructure.yml` runs (FR-04).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`actionlint` returns 0 errors on the fixed file.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Root cause documented in commit message.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md task 011 status updated to ✅.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The "0s loader-failure with empty jobs" pattern is the diagnostic signature of a YAML parse problem. If yamllint shows no duplicate keys but ghost triggers persist, check whether `paths:` is correctly nested under `pull_request:` (not `push:`) — push filters paths differently from pull_request and the spec wants only matching-path triggers to fire.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Load knowledge files. Rigor: STANDARD. Parallel-safe with 010 and 012.</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
